From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Materialise IOBuffer view before writing to a file

IOBuffer.save_to_file wrote the raw cppyy LowLevelView over the buffer
directly to the file handler. io.BytesIO tolerates that buffer-protocol
object, but a real io.BufferedWriter memcpy's from it and segfaults
(demo01_io.py). Materialise it to bytes first.
---
--- a/pyext/wrapper_cppyy/root_pythonizer.py
+++ b/pyext/wrapper_cppyy/root_pythonizer.py
@@ -108,7 +108,7 @@
         file_handler.write(pack(b'<L', self.length))
         data = ll.cast['uint8_t*'](self.start)
         data.reshape((self.length,))
-        file_handler.write(data)
+        file_handler.write(bytes(data))
 
     def load_from_file(self, file_handler: BufferedIOBase) -> bool:
         tmp = file_handler.read(1)
